581
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:44,510
Barry Goldwater's
Conscience of a Conservative.

582
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,200
Jan.
- Don't tell me.

583
00:32:46,300 --> 00:32:49,550
I worked on Gene McCarthy's
campaign. And voted for LBJ.

584
00:32:49,650 --> 00:32:51,400
Oh, no. No.

585
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:54,700
Well, looks like we're hitting it off
like grease hits the skillet.

586
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:57,400
Well, I don't think politics
should define a human being.

587
00:32:57,500 --> 00:32:59,900
There's more to people
than just how they vote.

588
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,000
I like that. I like that.
You're open-minded.

589
00:33:02,100 --> 00:33:05,000
Yeah, much more so than me,
I have to say.

590
00:33:05,100 --> 00:33:10,625
Well, I just think it's important to see
all sides of a situation.

591
00:33:12,300 --> 00:33:14,700
I read in the paper
that you're running for Congress.

592
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:16,100
Yes, ma'am, I am.

593
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:18,200
I don't believe in forcing myself on people.

594
00:33:18,300 --> 00:33:21,800
So that's why I'm just gonna ask
for your phone number, not your vote.

595
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:24,500
Oh, well,
I couldn't vote for you, anyway.

596
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:26,600
I live in Austin.

597
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:30,300
Not that I wouldn't consider it.

598
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:32,300
Well, thank you for that.

599
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:34,800
But if you win...
- Yeah?

600
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:37,790
please do something for education.

601
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:40,000
I was a teacher.
I believe that's the thing...

602
00:33:40,100 --> 00:33:42,300
...that can make a difference
in people's lives.

603
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:46,600
Well, I'll tell you what. If I win,
you can be my education advisor.

604
00:33:46,700 --> 00:33:48,700
Yeah, right.
- No, no, no. I'm serious.

605
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:51,775
I like the way you think, you know?

606
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:54,100
And look.

607
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:58,000
You're a devil.

608
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:02,500
Devil in a white hat.

609
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:08,600
My daddy and granddaddy were farmers.

610
00:34:08,700 --> 00:34:11,200
They didn't have anything to do
with this mess we're in.

611
00:34:11,300 --> 00:34:14,600
Bush's daddy and granddaddy have
been in politics his whole life.

612
00:34:14,700 --> 00:34:16,900
They don't know what
people's suffering is about.

613
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:19,800
George Bush here
hasn't earned the living he enjoys.

614
00:34:19,900 --> 00:34:22,200
I stand on my own two feet,
make my own living.

615
00:34:22,300 --> 00:34:24,400
When it comes to the integrity
of my father...

616
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:26,100
...what mess are you talking about?

617
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:27,600
Washington is the way it is...

618
00:34:27,700 --> 00:34:31,600
...because of the Yale and Harvard
fellas running the place.

619
00:34:31,700 --> 00:34:34,000
I went to Texas Tech,
you went to Yale.

620
00:34:34,100 --> 00:34:36,400
I went to UT Law,
you went to Harvard.

621
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:39,850
I've spent half my life in Midland.
I know the problems of the people here.

622
00:34:39,950 --> 00:34:41,600
Yeah, maybe at the country club.

623
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:44,000
You're still an outsider
as far as we're concerned.

624
00:34:44,100 --> 00:34:45,500
Mr. Hance will be nothing...

625
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:48,000
...but a tax-and-spend errand boy
for the Democrats...

626
00:34:48,100 --> 00:34:50,300
And he's really a carpetbagger
from Connecticut.

627
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:52,900
That's below the belt, even for you.
- It's God's truth.

628
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:56,550
Carpetbagger? This is my home. I've
been here in Midland since I was 2.

629
00:34:56,650 --> 00:35:00,750
You're still an Easterner as far as we're
concerned. East don't mix with Texas.

630
00:35:00,850 --> 00:35:02,000
My fellow Christians...

631
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:04,650
My fellow Christians
everywhere from Odessa to Lubbock...

632
00:35:04,750 --> 00:35:07,800
...last week, Mr. Bush here used
some of his vast sums of money...

633
00:35:07,900 --> 00:35:11,200
...to throw a beer bash
for underage students at Texas Tech.

634
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:12,400
A Bush Bash.

635
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:14,800
He's trying to get students to vote for him...

636
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:18,000
...by offering free alcohol to them.
Bribing them with booze.

637
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:20,300
Well, you've had a beer or two
in your lifetime.

638
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:22,400
Hell, yeah, but I'm not drinking with kids.

639
00:35:22,500 --> 00:35:24,500
That may be the cool thing to do at Yale...

640
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:26,900
...but not here in good Christian country.

641
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,200
He just kept hammering away at me,
you know?

642
00:35:29,300 --> 00:35:32,850
The same lame stuff, tarring and
feathering me about my father.

643
00:35:32,950 --> 00:35:35,400
My father. What am I supposed to do?
Run as Sam Smith?

644
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:40,050
Your family name has its advantages
and its disadvantages, W.

645
00:35:40,150 --> 00:35:42,400
Now, I'd still be with you
if you were Sam Smith.

646
00:35:42,500 --> 00:35:45,300
There's gotta be intelligent people
that can see through him.

647
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:48,100
They should,
but he was so busy attacking you.

648
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:53,100
I got in some licks before he threw
the dirty tricks there at the end. Right?

649
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:56,500
Well...
- What, you don't agree?

650
00:35:58,500 --> 00:36:01,600
Your mother told me never to criticize
a politician's speech.

651
00:36:01,700 --> 00:36:03,700
Honey, look, I got a thick hide.

652
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:06,400
You can tell me the truth.

653
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:08,500
Come on.

654
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,100
What, it was all bad?

655
00:36:13,100 --> 00:36:15,100
It wasn't good.

656
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:26,600
Why did you do that?

657
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:30,600
That was crazy.

658
00:36:30,700 --> 00:36:32,400
I told you I can take criticism.

659
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:35,900
You see, I'm already over it.
- The car isn't.

660
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:39,100
Do not ask me for my opinion
on your speeches again.

661
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:43,350
Honey, look, I'm gonna be asking you
for a long, long time.

662
00:36:43,450 --> 00:36:45,300
Not while we're driving then, please.

663
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:48,000
I never dated a woman quite like you,
you know that?

664
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:49,800
Hey, I think...

665
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:51,700
I think you are the gal for me.

666
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:54,400
Look, you're one of
the greatest listeners I've ever met.

667
00:36:54,500 --> 00:36:57,650
And since I'm one of the biggest
talkers, it seems like a genuine fit.

668
00:36:57,750 --> 00:36:59,750
What do you think, huh?

669
00:37:00,600 --> 00:37:03,500
It kind of does.
- Only kind of?

670
00:37:09,400 --> 00:37:12,000
More than kind of.
- Yeah.

671
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:19,050
The polls have now closed and
it looks like Democrat Kent Hance...

672
00:37:19,150 --> 00:37:22,200
...has defeated Republican candidate
George W. Bush...

673
00:37:22,300 --> 00:37:25,150
...in the race for
the 19th Congressional District.

674
00:37:25,250 --> 00:37:30,050
