977
00:55:59,650 --> 00:56:02,400
No matter what I do,
it's just never gonna be enough.

978
00:56:02,500 --> 00:56:04,500
Okay? Never.

979
00:56:07,200 --> 00:56:09,200
What's the bottom line, George?

980
00:56:09,300 --> 00:56:10,600
That Baghdad has...

981
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:13,650
...chemical and biological weapons
currently active, no question.

982
00:56:13,750 --> 00:56:15,600
Nukes? In some stage or other?

983
00:56:15,700 --> 00:56:18,100
That's still problematic, sir.
We say not yet...

984
00:56:18,200 --> 00:56:22,850
...but with moderate confidence we can
say they will have them by 2007, 2009.

985
00:56:22,950 --> 00:56:25,800
But definitely this guy
has got anthrax, mustard gas...

986
00:56:25,900 --> 00:56:29,300
...sarin, VX,
as much as 500 tons of CBW.

987
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:32,850
Given the dual-use provisions of the
U.N. sanctions, we can't prove intent.

988
00:56:32,950 --> 00:56:34,000
Until he launches.

989
00:56:34,100 --> 00:56:36,750
Their military is deteriorated,
infrastructure is shattered...

990
00:56:36,850 --> 00:56:40,600
Why is British Intelligence
telling us now that this guy...

991
00:56:40,700 --> 00:56:44,650
...is trying to buy up a few hundred
tons of yellow cake from Niger?

992
00:56:44,750 --> 00:56:46,700
We still have no backup on that.
- We don't.

993
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:50,400
Well, we know this:

994
00:56:50,700 --> 00:56:54,650
That Saddam is talking to Zarqawi,
who is talking to al Qaeda...

995
00:56:54,750 --> 00:56:58,050
...and Atta met Saddam's
intel chief in Czechoslovakia.

996
00:56:58,150 --> 00:57:01,000
There is no doubt that they're linked.

997
00:57:01,100 --> 00:57:02,500
No doubt, Dick?

998
00:57:02,600 --> 00:57:04,600
No doubt at all?

999
00:57:06,000 --> 00:57:08,300
No doubt, Colin.

1000
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:13,700
What do you say, Rummy?

1001
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:16,750
Sir, the absence of evidence
is not the evidence of absence.

1002
00:57:16,850 --> 00:57:20,800
Just because you do not have
evidence that something does exist...

1003
00:57:20,900 --> 00:57:22,100
...does not mean you have...

1004
00:57:22,200 --> 00:57:24,500
Can your intel say where these WMDs are?

1005
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:30,635
Well, my people think they've found
something in the area around Tikrit.

1006
00:57:31,900 --> 00:57:34,300
But we also have leads around Baghdad.

1007
00:57:34,400 --> 00:57:38,500
And to the areas east, west,
south, and north somewhat.

1008
00:57:38,600 --> 00:57:40,900
Well, let's find them, Rummy.
- Indeed.

1009
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:42,800
We know this guy Saddam's hiding stuff.

1010
00:57:42,900 --> 00:57:45,700
We know the U.N.'s
one big international mosh pit.

1011
00:57:45,800 --> 00:57:48,400
We got a lot of maybes, probablys
and buts from George...

1012
00:57:48,500 --> 00:57:50,300
...which John Q. Public ain't gonna buy.

1013
00:57:50,400 --> 00:57:53,600
We can present better,
but we don't have nukes.

1014
00:57:53,700 --> 00:57:55,900
What we have is a slam-dunk on the others.

1015
00:57:56,000 --> 00:57:57,000
Slam-dunk?

1016
00:57:57,100 --> 00:57:59,300
What have you been drinking,
Brother George?

1017
00:57:59,400 --> 00:58:01,400
What you need
is to bring in some lawyers...

1018
00:58:01,500 --> 00:58:03,500
...who can argue cases with juries to help.

1019
00:58:03,600 --> 00:58:05,500
These snapshots and Iraqi gobbledygook...

1020
00:58:05,600 --> 00:58:07,900
...on tape is just another bunch of bullshit.

1021
00:58:08,000 --> 00:58:11,485
Sir, you know,
whatever we come up with...

1022
00:58:14,301 --> 00:58:15,301
The old Europe.

1023
00:58:15,401 --> 00:58:17,501
Your father went to the U.N.,
Mr. President...

1024
00:58:17,601 --> 00:58:21,201
...and it took him six months, as I
remember, but he got his resolution.

1025
00:58:21,301 --> 00:58:22,501
And he got Congress too.

1026
00:58:22,601 --> 00:58:25,701
My gosh, Colin, you're the finest
military man in this room...

1027
00:58:25,801 --> 00:58:27,101
...we all know that.

1028
00:58:27,201 --> 00:58:30,501
But don't you think the Gulf War
days are long gone?

1029
00:58:30,601 --> 00:58:34,451
Do we really need six months
and half a million men...

1030
00:58:34,551 --> 00:58:37,851
...to knock off a tin-pot dictator
with a ragtag army?

1031
00:58:37,951 --> 00:58:39,801
You're right, Don,
I am a military man.

1032
00:58:39,901 --> 00:58:43,401
And you more than anyone in this room...

1033
00:58:43,501 --> 00:58:46,401
...learned the lessons of Vietnam.

1034
00:58:48,101 --> 00:58:51,201
Now, I think we're all adults in this room...

1035
00:58:51,301 --> 00:58:56,351
...and we recognize that 9l11,
no matter how horrific it was...

1036
00:58:56,451 --> 00:58:57,501
...and it was...

1037
00:58:57,601 --> 00:59:02,616
...was also an opportunity this time
for us to get it right.

1038
00:59:03,001 --> 00:59:05,001
Drain the swamp.

1039
00:59:05,101 --> 00:59:09,951
Sweep up all the bad guys in one big move.

1040
00:59:10,051 --> 00:59:12,101
Things related and not.

1041
00:59:12,501 --> 00:59:15,391
Otherwise, sir, they will be back.

1042
00:59:15,451 --> 00:59:17,401
I thought we just did that in Afghanistan.

1043
00:59:17,501 --> 00:59:19,401
We keep the focus
on sweeping up Bin Laden.

1044
00:59:19,501 --> 00:59:23,751
Goodness gracious, if you want
to call Afghanistan a war, Colin.

1045
00:59:23,851 --> 00:59:26,851
You know there were no real targets
to bomb there.

1046
00:59:26,951 --> 00:59:29,801
It was an exercise.
- In any case...

1047
00:59:29,901 --> 00:59:33,401
...if we don't act,
all of us will be out of here in 2004.

1048
00:59:33,501 --> 00:59:35,101
And that's the bottom line.

1049
00:59:35,201 --> 00:59:37,001
So this is all about politics, Karl?

1050
00:59:37,101 --> 00:59:39,601
I'm confused
as to what you're doing in this room.

1051
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:41,301
Okay, let's stay on message here.

1052
00:59:41,401 --> 00:59:44,301
Look, Genius Boy is just here
to listen, not talk.

1053
00:59:44,401 --> 00:59:46,401
You see, sir...

1054
00:59:46,901 --> 00:59:49,001
...what I'm pressing for here...

1055
00:59:49,101 --> 00:59:51,101
...is why?

1056
00:59:51,501 --> 00:59:53,501
Why are we doing this?

1057
00:59:54,101 --> 00:59:55,401
Why Iraq?

1058
00:59:55,501 --> 00:59:58,001
Why now?
- We discussed that already, Colin.

1059
00:59:58,101 --> 01:00:01,901
We had America
protected September 11 th.

1060
01:00:02,001 --> 01:00:04,751
That is, if people had been
doing their jobs right.

1061
01:00:04,851 --> 01:00:06,701
But we blew it.

1062
01:00:06,801 --> 01:00:10,601
And now instead of taking down
these 10,000 al Qaeda lunatics...

1063
01:00:10,701 --> 01:00:13,001
...in the mountains
with special operations...

1064
01:00:13,101 --> 01:00:15,201
...we're way outside of the box
on this thing.

1065
01:00:15,301 --> 01:00:18,191
Why aren't we trusting the system?

1066
01:00:18,901 --> 01:00:20,701
Why have we veered off to this place...

1067
01:00:20,801 --> 01:00:24,301
...where we accept without debate
that a preemptive strike on Iraq...

1068
01:00:24,401 --> 01:00:26,801
...can defeat terrorism
better than police action...

1069
01:00:26,901 --> 01:00:28,901
...or intel agencies that share information?

1070
01:00:29,001 --> 01:00:32,501
I just don't get it, Mr. President,
I don't. Because I am a soldier.

1071
01:00:32,601 --> 01:00:37,001
And I'd be mighty sure before
I put young American lives at risk.

1072
01:00:37,101 --> 01:00:40,151
Here we are...
- Okay, Secretary Powell, come on.

1073
01:00:40,251 --> 01:00:42,701
Let me finish.

1074
01:00:45,001 --> 01:00:46,701
Here we are...

1075
01:00:46,801 --> 01:00:50,371
...changing the whole way
we do business...

1076
01:00:50,401 --> 01:00:55,051
...in response to a small but dedicated
enemy hiding out in caves and jungles.

1077
01:00:55,151 --> 01:01:00,591
Are we losing our perspective here?
- We changed our perspective.

1078
01:01:01,201 --> 01:01:03,501
The Trade Center was bombed in '93.

1079
01:01:03,601 --> 01:01:06,201
We had a huge attack on Oklahoma in '95.

1080
01:01:06,301 --> 01:01:09,401
And those who did it are in jail or dead.

1081
01:01:09,501 --> 01:01:11,001
Big difference.

1082
01:01:11,101 --> 01:01:16,501
Oklahoma terrorists
didn't have anthrax or nukes.

1083
01:01:17,001 --> 01:01:18,201
Colin...

1084
01:01:18,301 --> 01:01:21,301
...I swear, you're beginning
to sound like Neville Chamberlain.

1085
01:01:21,401 --> 01:01:23,401
Oh, don't patronize me,
Mr. Five Deferments.

1086
01:01:23,501 --> 01:01:26,201
You save that for speeches
to veterans. Neville Chamberlain.

1087
01:01:26,301 --> 01:01:27,901
You think, really...

1088
01:01:28,001 --> 01:01:31,351
You think,
with all your diplomatic bullshit...

1089
01:01:31,451 --> 01:01:37,146
...that you can appease Islamic
fascists, who are as nuts as Hitler.

1090
01:01:38,001 --> 01:01:40,601
You wanna know what I see,
Mr. President?

1091
01:01:40,701 --> 01:01:43,701
I see a world where in about 25 years...

1092
01:01:43,801 --> 01:01:46,436
...America's reserves are gone.

1093
01:01:47,301 --> 01:01:48,401
Done.

1094
01:01:48,501 --> 01:01:49,601
Demand is up...

1095
01:01:49,701 --> 01:01:51,201
...30, 40 percent.

1096
01:01:51,301 --> 01:01:56,751
And we have two oceans
blocking us from the world reserves.

1097
01:01:56,851 --> 01:02:00,166
You think we're gonna have allies then?

1098
01:02:00,301 --> 01:02:03,001
We're at 5 percent
of the world's population.

1099
01:02:03,101 --> 01:02:06,451
We use 25 percent of its energy.

1100
01:02:06,551 --> 01:02:09,201
You think Russia and China
are gonna help us out...

1101
01:02:09,301 --> 01:02:12,301
...when they need
those resources themselves?

1102
01:02:12,401 --> 01:02:16,051
Eighty percent of the world's
future energy reserves...

1103
01:02:16,151 --> 01:02:20,751
...are right here in Eurasia,
where the prize ultimately lies.

1104
01:02:20,851 --> 01:02:23,801
Oil, gas, water.

1105
01:02:24,501 --> 01:02:28,001
Iraq alone,
10 percent of the world's reserves...

1106
01:02:28,101 --> 01:02:32,351
...60 of 80 oil fields are still undeveloped.

1107
01:02:32,451 --> 01:02:35,401
And probably another 100 billion
gallons in their western desert.

1108
01:02:35,501 --> 01:02:37,901
They are floating in a sea of oil.
- We have bases...

1109
01:02:38,001 --> 01:02:40,801
...in more than 120 countries
all over the world.

1110
01:02:40,901 --> 01:02:44,046
If we include Iraq,
look what happens.

1111
01:02:46,101 --> 01:02:50,301
We are at the fertile
choke point of civilization.

1112
01:02:50,401 --> 01:02:53,751
The Tigris-Euphrates,
the biblical cradle.

1113
01:02:53,851 --> 01:02:56,826
We drain this swamp, like Don says.

1114
01:02:56,901 --> 01:02:58,401
We rebuild it.

1115
01:02:58,501 --> 01:03:00,501
We develop its resources to the maximum.

1116
01:03:00,601 --> 01:03:02,601
They own it, we run it.

1117
01:03:02,601 --> 01:03:06,101
Pipelines, sea lanes, their resources
finance the reconstruction.

1118
01:03:06,201 --> 01:03:09,701
A nexus of power that won't be broken
in our lifetime.

1119
01:03:09,801 --> 01:03:12,101
If we stick to the plan.

1120
01:03:12,601 --> 01:03:16,681
So, what is our real exit strategy
on Iraq, Dick?

1121
01:03:22,401 --> 01:03:24,401
There is no exit.

1122
01:03:27,101 --> 01:03:29,101
We stay.

1123
01:03:34,701 --> 01:03:36,911
Spoken like a true oilman.

1124
01:03:37,301 --> 01:03:39,851
You were part of the plan, Colin,
back in the '90s.

1125
01:03:39,951 --> 01:03:43,201
You backed our dominance in
weaponry, space, cyber, electronic.

1126
01:03:43,301 --> 01:03:45,101
You agreed that we would never allow...

1127
01:03:45,201 --> 01:03:48,001
...another military-economic rival
to emerge against us again.

1128
01:03:48,101 --> 01:03:50,201
I don't understand...
- Turning weapons loose...

1129
01:03:50,301 --> 01:03:53,401
...on terrorists is like trying to hit
an ant with an elephant gun.

1130
01:03:53,501 --> 01:03:56,151
We invoke preemption...
Preventive war, you call it.

1131
01:03:56,251 --> 01:03:58,201
The right to use nukes whenever we see fit.

1132
01:03:58,301 --> 01:04:01,951
and I guarantee you, Paul,
we will be in a forever war everywhere.

1133
01:04:02,051 --> 01:04:04,346
Three, four wars at a time.

1134
01:04:04,401 --> 01:04:07,501
That's not new world order,
that's a world gone mad.

1135
01:04:07,601 --> 01:04:10,101
There's got to be some
global cooperation here.

1136
01:04:10,201 --> 01:04:12,901
No one's against cooperation,
Colin, you know that.

1137
01:04:13,001 --> 01:04:16,501
As long as we're calling the shots.
- Which gets us back to reality.

1138
01:04:16,601 --> 01:04:18,601
Lest we forget...

1139
01:04:19,601 --> 01:04:21,901
...where do you see
a lack of American presence?

1140
01:04:22,001 --> 01:04:23,501
Right in the heart of it all.

1141
01:04:23,601 --> 01:04:25,601
What's missing?

1142
01:04:26,701 --> 01:04:28,701
Iran.

1143
01:04:29,401 --> 01:04:30,601
The mother lode.

1144
01:04:30,701 --> 01:04:33,601
Third largest oil reserve in the world.

1145
01:04:33,701 --> 01:04:36,701
Forty percent of the world's oil...

1146
01:04:36,801 --> 01:04:40,101
...goes right through here,
the Strait of Hormuz.

1147
01:04:40,201 --> 01:04:44,281
Control Iran, control Eurasia,
control the world.

1148
01:04:45,101 --> 01:04:47,101
Empire.

1149
01:04:47,801 --> 01:04:50,001
Real empire.

1150
01:04:50,701 --> 01:04:53,336
Nobody will fuck with us again.

1151
01:04:58,901 --> 01:05:02,131
It's big, Vice.
You know, big thoughts.

1152
01:05:03,601 --> 01:05:07,351
But you go out here and you
scare people when you talk like that.

1153
01:05:07,451 --> 01:05:09,901
The working Joe's not thinking about oil.

1154
01:05:10,001 --> 01:05:12,801
We're talking 9l11 terrorists...

1155
01:05:12,901 --> 01:05:14,501
...WMDs.

1156
01:05:14,601 --> 01:05:17,801
We're talking freedom and democracy.

1157
01:05:17,901 --> 01:05:20,196
We're talking Axis of Evil.

1158
01:05:20,201 --> 01:05:21,801
Sir...

1159
01:05:21,901 --> 01:05:24,701
...you have the touch, not I.

1160
01:05:30,301 --> 01:05:32,301
You know,
when I was coming up...

1161
01:05:32,401 --> 01:05:34,501
...it was a dangerous world.

1162
01:05:34,601 --> 01:05:37,701
But we knew exactly who the 'they' were.

1163
01:05:37,801 --> 01:05:41,951
We knew it was us versus them,
and it was clear who 'them' was.

1164
01:05:42,051 --> 01:05:43,701
Today...

1165
01:05:43,801 --> 01:05:48,101
...we're not so sure who the 'they' are,
but we know they're there.

1166
01:05:48,201 --> 01:05:50,001
Now, I'm not gonna negotiate with myself.

1167
01:05:50,101 --> 01:05:52,001
I'm a gut player, always have been.

1168
01:05:52,101 --> 01:05:54,901
And I am just so bone-tired of this Saddam.

1169
01:05:55,001 --> 01:05:57,101
He's always misunderestimated me.

1170
01:05:57,201 --> 01:05:59,701
I don't want our soldiers
invading in that desert heat.

1171
01:05:59,801 --> 01:06:02,501
We have got to get this war
going before summer, Rummy.

1172
01:06:02,601 --> 01:06:06,151
You say go now, sir, and Tommy
can start mobilizing normally.

1173
01:06:06,251 --> 01:06:08,501
We could have 300,000 troops in the Gulf...

1174
01:06:08,601 --> 01:06:11,201
...by early January without creating a stir.

1175
01:06:11,301 --> 01:06:13,301
I want you to keep a tight lid on it, Rummy.

1176
01:06:13,401 --> 01:06:16,401
For the record, this is against
the spirit of the U.N. resolution.

1177
01:06:16,501 --> 01:06:19,351
We agreed with our allies
to let the inspectors do their jobs.

1178
01:06:19,451 --> 01:06:23,191
As Yogi Berra said,
'Dיjא vu all over again.'

1179
01:06:24,001 --> 01:06:26,001
Colin, you know what a burn card is?

1180
01:06:26,101 --> 01:06:27,501
No, sir.

1181
01:06:27,601 --> 01:06:30,701
Someday I gotta teach you
how to play some Texas Hold 'Em.

1182
01:06:30,801 --> 01:06:32,801
You keep selling our friends at the U. N...

1183
01:06:32,901 --> 01:06:36,551
...but whatever they say, in the end,
the final decision is mine.

1184
01:06:36,651 --> 01:06:38,201
Yes, sir.

1185
01:06:38,301 --> 01:06:42,636
Now, are you gonna be with us
on this, Colin, right?

1186
01:06:46,401 --> 01:06:48,601
I'm with you, sir.
- Good.

1187
01:06:49,201 --> 01:06:51,201
All right, gentlemen,
it's a great meeting.

1188
01:06:51,301 --> 01:06:52,301
Best yet.

1189
01:06:52,401 --> 01:06:54,401
Let's close this out.

1190
01:07:08,401 --> 01:07:10,501
Well, you've done a heck of a job, son.

1191
01:07:10,601 --> 01:07:13,321
Even though I traded Sammy Sosa?

1192
01:07:13,501 --> 01:07:15,701
We all make mistakes.

1193
01:07:16,101 --> 01:07:19,001
Center field. This is my favorite spot
in the world, Poppy.

1194
01:07:19,101 --> 01:07:22,601
You know, whenever things get rough,
when I need to clear my head...

1195
01:07:22,701 --> 01:07:26,101
...I just come out here.
It just makes me feel at peace.

1196
01:07:26,201 --> 01:07:28,901
Right now,
I wish I had a spot like this.

1197
01:07:29,001 --> 01:07:31,501
Not the White House lawn.

1198
01:07:31,601 --> 01:07:34,451
This guy Saddam's really put a burr
under your saddle, I guess?

1199
01:07:34,551 --> 01:07:36,801
Saddam, what I call him now.

1200
01:07:36,901 --> 01:07:39,301
If you emphasize the first syllable...

1201
01:07:39,401 --> 01:07:42,901
...it means in Arabic, 'the little boy
who shines old men's shoes.'

1202
01:07:43,001 --> 01:07:45,601
Well, he's one shoe-shining
piece of crap, all right.

1203
01:07:45,701 --> 01:07:47,701
He gassed his own people,
the Kurds...

1204
01:07:47,801 --> 01:07:49,901
...invades Kuwait.

1205
01:07:50,001 --> 01:07:52,601
It's time to back him down
and take him out, Poppy.

1206
01:07:52,701 --> 01:07:54,501
You know, like you done Noriega.

1207
01:07:54,601 --> 01:07:55,701
Well, you know...

1208
01:07:55,801 --> 01:07:59,301
...I've always believed in leaving
personal feelings out of politics...

1209
01:07:59,401 --> 01:08:02,251
...but Saddam, this can't stand.

1210
01:08:02,351 --> 01:08:04,501
I'm not gonna let that little dictator control...

1211
01:08:04,601 --> 01:08:07,501
...one quarter of the civilized world's oil.

1212
01:08:07,601 --> 01:08:09,501
I got a feeling about this.

1213
01:08:09,601 --> 01:08:11,601
How I handle it...

1214
01:08:11,701 --> 01:08:15,701
...one way or another, is gonna
determine my legacy as president.

